&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Appier &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Appier is a software-as-a-service (SaaS) company that uses artificial intelligence (AI) to power business decision-making. Founded in 2012 with a vision of democratizing AI, Appier’s mission is turning AI into ROI by making software intelligent. Appier now has 17 offices across APAC, Europe and U.S., and is listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange (Ticker number: 4180). Visit&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.appier.com&quot;&gt; www.appier.com&lt;/a&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Global ESS Sales Operations Manager / Associate Manager&lt;/strong&gt; will act as a key business partner for Global ESS Sales Operations, supporting revenue forecast discipline and end-to-end operational governance across GCR, JP, KR, and SEA. This role is designed as a second owner for Global ESS Sales Ops.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will co-manage two major pillars: &lt;strong&gt;Revenue Forecast&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Operation&lt;/strong&gt;. The person should be able to connect business context, Salesforce data, contract readiness, pricing governance, and cross-functional execution to improve revenue visibility and operational quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. Revenue Forecast &amp;amp; Management Reporting&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support weekly and monthly tracking of target attainment, backlog status, pipeline movement, renewal progress, and revenue realization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review forecast assumptions, close dates, activation dates, deal stages, and pipeline hygiene to improve forecast accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare regional and global business updates, deal risk summaries, forecast variance analysis, and management reporting materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track renewal, upsell, downgrade, churn, and activation risks to support leadership decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. Operation Governance &amp;amp; Deal Review&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own first-level deal review for New, Upsell, Renewal, Downgrade, Churn, and special pricing cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review Salesforce opportunity data, including MRR, ACV, product scope, contract period, activation date, billing terms, discount rate, and approval status.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Salesforce data hygiene by collaborating with relevant stakeholders to clean, validate, and maintain CRM data, ensuring data accuracy and reliable reporting output.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate pricing structure, discount level, margin status, approval path, and required supporting evidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify low-margin deals, pricing exceptions, special terms, and contract risks; prepare escalation summaries for management review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure operational consistency across regions while maintaining flexibility for region-specific commercial needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. Contract Readiness &amp;amp; Cross-functional Coordination&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment among Salesforce data, approved commercial terms, service scope, report logic, and financial reporting before contract issuance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Sales, CSM, Legal, Finance, Product, Strategy, and MIS teams to resolve deal blockers and execution risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track pending approvals, missing information, contract review status, and operational blockers to support timely deal closure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4. AI-enabled and Continuously Evolving Sales Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools to improve Sales Operations efficiency, including SFDC data validation, forecast summary generation, pricing case comparison, meeting preparation, documentation, and recurring issue analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Global Compensation Specialist designs, implements, and administers international compensation programs and policies across APAC, EMEA, and the US. This role drives annual salary cycles, conducts market benchmarking, and provides expert consultation to HR partners and business leaders to ensure competitive, equitable, and compliant pay practices aligned with corporate strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in total rewards, including cash, equity, benefits,&amp;nbsp; incentive allowances with a comprehensive understanding of how diverse pay components strategically drive business goals and talent motivation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute complex compensation analyses and build dashboards (e.g., Talent ROI) to inform pay decisions and retention strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage global salary survey participation and benchmarking (e.g., Mercer, WTW, Radford) to maintain market competitiveness. Familiar with survey companies methodology and job architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key contributor in annual salary and bonus review cycles, including project management, data validation, and communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design, modeling, and administration of Short-Term (STI) and Long-Term Incentive (LTI) programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HR Business Partners to provide data-driven recommendations on off-cycle adjustments and compensation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize current compensation policies to drive business growth and enhance talent motivation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in HR, Finance, Economics, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of progressive compensation experience in a multinational environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel and experience with HRIS and data visualization platforms (e.g., Workday, HiBob, Power BI, Tableau, Looker). Demonstrated ability to leverage AI tools to automate reporting, improve data accuracy, generate workforce insights, and enhance HR operational effectiveness.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in job evaluation, salary structure design, and incentive plan administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional analytical, project management, and stakeholder communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated strong problem-solving capabilities to address complex organizational compensation challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-AC2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role — Workforce &amp;amp; Equity Operations Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a proactive, detail-oriented Specialist to drive HR operations across &lt;strong&gt;Time &amp;amp; Workforce Operations&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Global Equity Administration&lt;/strong&gt;. Based in Taiwan within the Employee Experience team, you will collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders and external vendors to ensure accurate, compliant tracking of global attendance and equity data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Appier, we value innovation and career agility. We encourage every team member to challenge existing processes and leverage AI and automation to build smarter, more scalable HR operations. We welcome open-minded individuals who thrive in a shifting landscape and view change as an opportunity to grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time &amp;amp; Workforce Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attendance &amp;amp; Shift Management&lt;/strong&gt;: Oversee global employee attendance and leave administration, maintain shift and on-call schedules to ensure seamless operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Integrity &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;: Generate regular attendance reports to ensure accurate, compliant data provision for payroll processing and auditing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Process Automation&lt;/strong&gt;: Continuously optimize workforce operations and leverage AI tools to automate routine workflows while ensuring governance and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor &amp;amp; Lifecycle Support&lt;/strong&gt;: Manage attendance/equity vendors (SLAs and invoicing) and deliver timely support for routine HR inquiries and certificates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equity &amp;amp; Stock Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESOP Administration&lt;/strong&gt;: Administer global employee equity programs, ensuring accurate transaction processing, vesting records, and data integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reconciliation &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;: Prepare monthly ESOP transaction reports, ensuring high accuracy and compliance for subsequent payroll and financial auditing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workflow Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;: Identify process bottlenecks and apply AI solutions to transform manual equity administration into scalable operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in HR lifecycle service delivery, international HR operations, or global equity administration is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional communicator with a service-oriented mindset, strong ownership, meticulous attention to detail, and proven abilities to effectively prioritize deliverables in a fast-paced, evolving environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and analytical skills with high resilience and learning agility to independently navigate ambiguity and embrace new organizational challenges.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open-mindedness and enthusiasm for exploring and implementing AI/automation tools to optimize manual HR workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English proficiency required; additional languages is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-AC2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; We are seeking a motivated and creative individual to join our team as a Part-Time / Intern for interactive creative production. In this role, you will support the development of interactive advertising creatives, including playables and mobile ad experiences. This is an excellent opportunity for someone passionate about mobile gaming and digital media, and looking to gain hands-on experience in the advertising and creative tech industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the ideation and creation of interactive advertising creatives for mobile campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with pre-sales, product marketing, and product managers to iterate on creative concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct research on industry trends, competitor ads, and mobile gaming experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback and contribute ideas on gameplay mechanics, visual layouts, and interactive flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing creative assets or content documents, and help with basic QA/testing of interactive ads. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; No specific background required (Bachelor’s or Master’s students are welcome).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Availability:&lt;/strong&gt; Must be available at least 3 days per week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Language Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Proficient in English (speaking, reading, and writing); able to communicate ideas clearly in both English and Mandarin.&lt;/li&gt;
