&lt;h3&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[The seniority/title is determined by job-related skills, experience, and evaluation after the interview.]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring &lt;strong&gt;Product Builders&lt;/strong&gt; to shape the future of &lt;strong&gt;marketing for agents&lt;/strong&gt; — where AI agents are no longer tools, but active participants in how products are built, decisions are made, and value is delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI agents are fundamentally reshaping:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;how products are built (AI-native, faster, more iterative)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;how marketing flows work (agent-driven discovery, decisioning, and execution)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;how brands and customers communicate (from campaigns → conversations → autonomous interactions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This shift unlocks a new wave of opportunities — to redesign workflows, reimagine user experiences, and build entirely new product categories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a traditional PM / designer / engineer / GTM role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll operate as a builder at the frontier, using vibe coding, AI tools, and rapid prototyping to explore and ship products in this emerging space. You won’t just define what to build — you’ll build, test, and evolve it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build, not just define&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and ship products — where agents discover, decide, and act on behalf of users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ship fast, learn fast — iterate based on simulation or real usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own problems end-to-end&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify meaningful problems worth solving (clear “why this matters”).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive from discovery → prototype → launch → iteration → scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operate with high agency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Don’t wait for perfect clarity — create momentum, test hypotheses, and move forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of outcomes, not just outputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Redesign how brands and customers interact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore new interaction models: agent-to-agent, human-in-the-loop, and autonomous workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reimagine marketing workflows as agent-driven systems, not static funnels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus on what truly matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify the core 1–3 things that make the product valuable, and execute them exceptionally well.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Avoid overbuilding — prioritize signal over noise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate to ship impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with engineering, design, data, and GTM as co-creators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously refine based on real-world feedback and data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Appier &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appier is a software-as-a-service (SaaS) company that uses artificial intelligence (AI) to power business decision-making. Founded in 2012 with a vision of democratizing AI, Appier’s mission is turning AI into ROI by making software intelligent. Appier now has 17 offices across APAC, Europe and U.S., and is listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange (Ticker number: 4180). Visit www.appier.com for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appier is seeking Software Engineers, QA Automation to ensure continuous delivery of high-quality system. You will work with engineers to design testing plans for various types of systems - large traffic distributed system, machine learning algorithm, big data platform, frontend system, etc. He/ She will master the skills in defining suitable test strategies and test automation for different types of systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[The seniority/title is determined by job-related skills, experience, and evaluation after the interview.]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;aLF-aPX-K0-aPE&quot;&gt;- 3+ years of experience in QA Engineering with a focus on automation and test strategy.&lt;br&gt;- Proficiency in scripting languages (e.g., JavaScript, Java, or similar) for writing automated tests.&lt;br&gt;- Hands-on experience with test automation frameworks (Playwright is a strong plus).&lt;br&gt;- Strong experience with API testing tools (Postman, RestAssured, or equivalents).&lt;br&gt;- Exposure to backend service testing (a plus).&lt;br&gt;- Experience in cross-browser and cross-platform compatibility testing.&lt;br&gt;- Mobile testing experience on both iOS and Android.&lt;br&gt;- Familiarity with performance testing concepts and tools (nice to have).&lt;br&gt;- Deep understanding of SDLC, Agile methodologies, and QA’s role in shaping product quality early in the cycle.&lt;br&gt;- Strong knowledge of test pyramid principles and best practices for balancing manual vs automated test coverage.&lt;br&gt;- Practical experience with Jira and TestRail (or similar test management tools).&lt;br&gt;- Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the confidence to question and propose improvements.&lt;br&gt;- Analytical mindset with strong problem-solving abilities.&lt;br&gt;- Self-discipline and adaptability to succeed in a remote-first environment.&lt;br&gt;- Ability to decide regression test coverage independently.&lt;br&gt;- Strong ownership of manual test efforts, complemented with automation where it adds most value.&lt;br&gt;- A questioning mindset that ensures no assumption goes untested.&lt;br&gt;- Availability in a timezone similar to European time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;#LI-Fully Remote&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;【About the role】&lt;br&gt;In the position of Quality Assurance Intern at Appier, you will be an integral part of our QA team, dedicated to ensuring the highest standards of software quality and reliability. This role provides a unique opportunity to delve into various aspects of software testing and quality control in a fast-paced and innovative tech environment.&lt;br&gt;We are currently looking for individuals who can commit to an internship schedule of 3-5 days (24-40 hours) per week. &lt;br&gt;This internship opportunity entails a minimum duration of 1 year, beginning from the present date. Students from the third year of undergraduate to the second year of master&#39;s program are welcome!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;【Responsibilities】&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manual Test Execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting bugs via JIRA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bug fix verification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exploratory Testing with guided charter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;(Advertising Cloud) Test the AD in App/Website, record the screen video and network traffic log(get from proxy server log) from click AD to open the destination product page.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;(Personalization Cloud, Data Cloud) Test the multi channel marketing automation service empowered by AI. Ensure integration between components or products. Find weak links in complex system architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;【About you】&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Minimum requirement -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to understand requirements, specifications, and follow the test steps written in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interested in learning new technology and solving real world problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A graduating student/BS in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Preferred qualifications -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in web and mobile application testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in HTTP Protocol and its functionality (RESTful API, Cookie, WebUI, ..)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Fiddler/Charles proxy server&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Postman/SoapUI HTTP test&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with programming using AI tools (such as GitHub Copilot, Cursor...) is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
